===Etymology 1===
(noun) Middle English ''[[lome]]''<Old English ''[[gelōma]]''<[[ge-]] ([[perfective]] [[prefix]]) + ''[[lōma]]'' ("[[utensil]], [[tool]]"), of unknown origin, akin to Middle Dutch ''[[allame]]'', "tool"

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

#See [[loon]], the bird.
#A [[frame]] or [[machine]] of wood or other material, in which a [[weaver]] forms [[cloth]] out of [[thread]]; a machine for interweaving yarn or threads into a fabric, as in knitting or lace making.
#That part of an [[oar]] which is near the [[grip]] or [[handle]] and [[inboard]] from the [[rowlock]].

====Translations====
;a frame in which to weave
*Swedish: [[vävstol]] {{c}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

#To [[impend]]; to [[threaten]] or hang over.
#:''The clouds '''loomed''' over the mountains.

